President Cyril Ramaphosa wants Western countries with excess COVID-19 vaccines to donate some to developing countries. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa wants Western countries with excess COVID-19 vaccines to donate some to developing countries. Ramaphosa is also calling for Africa to be able to produce more vaccines on its own. According to the World Health Organization, nearly 3.4 million people have been infected and over 85,000 have died. READ: COVID-19 | Ramaphosa calls for African-made vaccines The president attended summit with other African leaders and global financial institutions in Paris where "a New Deal for Africa and by Africa" was launched. The "New Deal" will use global financial firepower to replenish depleted coffers and ramp up a sluggish vaccine rollout. - Additional reporting AFP